page.title: 19PERSONALITIES-BRAISHFIELD
page.content:
LAWRIE McMENEMY,lived at Braishfield during the 7 years he was Manager of SOUTHAMPTON FOOTBALL CLUB, and still retains his property although he is now Manager of SUNDERLAND FOOTBALL CLUB.
GARY WINDEBANK lives at Lower Slackstead, and is well known for his strong-man feats.In the 1986 Guinness Book of Records,he is listed as holding the record for the greatest number of motor tyres supported in a free lift,the total being 96. This record is dated 1984. He appears at many charity and fund-raising events.
